Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.reflection.property.filters

Class BasePropertyFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.reflection.property.filters.BasePropertyFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropertyFilter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BeansProperties, KivaKitProperties
    public class BasePropertyFilter
extends java.lang.Object
implements PropertyFilter
    Base class for property filters. Supports Java Beans and KivaKit style accessor naming conventions with the enum BasePropertyFilter.NamingConvention and filtering of properties and fields with BasePropertyFilter.Include. The constructor takes a style and a set of explicit includes (nothing is included by default). Static fields and properties are never included. Any field or method tagged with KivaKitExcludeProperty will be excluded regardless of the inclusions specified.

    Subclasses can utilize the following tests to implement filters that don't follow the pattern implemented by this base class.

    Getters and Setters

    • isGetter(Method) - True if the method is a getter under the given naming convention
    • isSetter(Method) - True if the method is a setter under the given naming convention

    Include Tests

    • isIncluded(Method) - True if the method is included under the given set of BasePropertyFilter.Includes
    • isIncluded(Field) - True if the field is included under the given set of BasePropertyFilter.Includes

    KivaKit Annotation Tests

    • isKivaKitIncluded(Method) - True if the method is annotated with KivaKitIncludeProperty
    • isKivaKitIncluded(Field) - True if the field is annotated with KivaKitIncludeProperty
    • isKivaKitExcluded(Method) - True if the method is annotated with KivaKitExcludeProperty
    • isKivaKitExcluded(Field) - True if the field is annotated with KivaKitExcludeProperty
